<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,1106,1431]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,262,1106,1132]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<typeStatus box="[196,255,1106,1132]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Type</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
In Reitter’s collection at 
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34991" box="[565,658,1106,1132]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34991" name="Hungarian Natural History Museum (Termeszettudomanyi Muzeum)" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">HNHM</collectionCode>
, is the female 
<typeStatus box="[829,931,1106,1132]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">holotype</typeStatus>
(formerly pinned through the right elytron with a large pin which transversely cracked elytron, right middle leg missing, remounted on a paper card) bearing the handwritten labels: “Maderia, Fuente, Coll. Em. Friv.”, “ 
<taxonomicName box="[1036,1266,1181,1206]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="semilunatus" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[1036,1266,1181,1206]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Lixus semilunatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1275,1344,1181,1207]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Petri”, “Monotypus, 
<number box="[317,380,1218,1244]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="1904.0">1904</number>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Petri" authorityName="Petri" box="[394,680,1218,1244]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="semilunatus">
<emphasis box="[394,613,1219,1244]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Lixus semilunatus</emphasis>
Petri
</taxonomicName>
” red brimmed museum label, and “ 
<taxonomicName box="[1115,1378,1219,1244]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Conorhynchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mixtus">
<emphasis box="[1115,1378,1219,1244]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Conorhynchus mixtus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(F.), Gültekin det. 
<number box="[311,376,1256,1282]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="2008.0">2008</number>
”. It is the 
<typeStatus box="[492,595,1256,1282]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[634,845,1256,1281]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="semilunatus">
<emphasis box="[634,845,1256,1281]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Lixus semilunatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The 
<typeStatus box="[912,962,1256,1282]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">type</typeStatus>
locality is Maderia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,1106,1431]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,320,1293,1319]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was misidentified by 
<bibRefCitation author="Petri" box="[749,909,1293,1319]" pageId="18" pageNumber="21" refString="Petri, K. (1904 c) Funf neue Lixus - arten. Annales Musei Nationalis Hungarici, 2: 233 - 236." type="journal article" year="1904" yearSuffix="c">
Petri (
<number box="[823,886,1293,1319]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="1904.0">1904</number>
c)
</bibRefCitation>
at the generic as well as species level. It is conspecific with 
<taxonomicName authority="Fabricius" authorityName="Fabricius" box="[352,746,1330,1356]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Conorhynchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mixtus">
<emphasis box="[352,606,1331,1356]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Conorhynchus mixtus</emphasis>
(Fabricius)
</taxonomicName>
, as clarified by 
<bibRefCitation author="Gultekin" box="[934,1127,1330,1356]" pageId="18" pageNumber="20" refString="Gultekin, L. (2006) On some Lixinae types of J. C. Fabricius (Coleoptera, Curculionidae). Fragmenta entomologica, 38 (1): 111 - 133." type="journal article" year="2006">
Gültekin (
<number box="[1053,1118,1330,1356]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="2006.0">2006</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. Thus, a new combination and synonym is proposed here: 
<taxonomicName authority="Fabricius, 1792" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1792" box="[542,1028,1368,1394]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Conorhynchus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mixtus">
<emphasis box="[542,808,1368,1393]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Conorhynchus mixtus</emphasis>
(Fabricius, 
<number box="[956,1018,1368,1394]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="1792.0">1792</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
[= 
<taxonomicName authority="Petri, 1904" authorityName="Petri" authorityYear="1904" box="[1072,1437,1368,1394]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="semilunatus">
<emphasis box="[1072,1293,1368,1393]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Lixus semilunatus</emphasis>
Petri, 
<number box="[1376,1437,1368,1394]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="1904.0">1904</number>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,369,1405,1431]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">comb. and syn. n.</emphasis>
].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
